Unified Package Manager

The unified Package Manager is an attempt to use the same command line syntax and output with different *NIX package Manager. This version supports: apt-get (Debian and siblings), port (MacPorts) and pacman (Arch Linux). Experimental support for yum/rpm since Rev 101.

Currently supported Platforms:
  Debian (apt)
	OpenBSD (port)
	Darwin (MacPorts)
